        <chapter>                                                      <!--[1-N]-->
         <title>A tool Against Corruption of China</title>                                                  <!--[0-N]-->
           <paragraph>Catching Tigers and Flies, a part of the Xi Jinping’s
           anticorruption campaign against corruption that China’s
           President, Xi Jinping, launched shortly after he came to power in late 2012.</paragraph>
           <paragraph>Scything through all ranks of people, Xi’s deputies have
           felled officials of both high and low rank, or as Xi himself
           put it in a memorable phrase, both “tigers and flies.” To
           date, tens of thousands have been swept out of office.</paragraph>
           </chapter>
           <chapter>
           <title>Tigers and Flies</title>
           <paragraph>Tiger are party and governmental officials, sub-provincial/ministeral lever and military officers holding a rank of Major General. Flies are level officers and individuals.</paragraph>
