      <section>                                                         <!--[1-N]-->
          <title>Historical Break</title>
          <subtitle>After the 1929 Crash</subtitle>
          <chapter>                                                   <!--[0-N]-->
            <paragraph>The devaluation of the pound in 1931 and the dollar in 1934, after the crash of 1929,
              behaved an abrupt decrease in the gold content of these currencies and thus a significant
              increase in the price of gold.</paragraph>
            <paragraph>Depression of 1929 had devastating recessionary effects in both industrialized countries
              and in those commodity exporters with a general decline in demand and production.</paragraph>
          </chapter>
